Privacy Policy for BabyNames Hub

Effective Date: March 26, 2026

HorizonMyApps ("we," "our," or "us") operates the BabyNames Hub mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our App.

1. Information We Do Not Collect

We respect your privacy. We do not collect, store, or share any personal information such as your name, email address, contacts, or location data when you use the App.

The App is designed to work without requiring users to create accounts or submit personal data.

2. Third-Party Services

Although we do not collect personal data, the App uses third-party services to support functionality and provide a free experience.

Advertising (AdMob)

We use AdMob, a service provided by Google, to display ads within the App. AdMob may automatically collect certain information, including:

Device identifiers (such as advertising ID)
IP address
Device type, operating system, and browser details
Interaction data related to ads

This information is used to deliver and improve advertisements.

You can learn more about how Google handles data here:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

3. Advertising and Personalization

Ads shown in the App may be personalized based on your interests. You can control or disable personalized ads through your device settings:

On Android: Settings → Google → Ads
On iOS: Settings → Privacy & Security → Apple Advertising
4. Children’s Privacy

The App is intended for general audiences, including parents searching for baby names.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13. If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can promptly remove it.

5. Data Security

Since we do not collect or store personal data, we do not maintain user databases. However, we rely on trusted third-party services (like AdMob) that implement industry-standard security measures.

6. Your Rights

Because we do not collect personal information directly, we do not store data that can be accessed, corrected, or deleted.

For data collected by third-party services (such as Google), please refer to their privacy policies for your rights and options.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any updates will be reflected by revising the Effective Date above. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy.

